I really like all the different stores and that it's tucked back from Somerville Ave, it's quiet and you don't feel like you are near a busy street. I also really like the concept of the little restaurants where there are a lot of options so if you have a group everyone can get what they want. It's a good place to go if you want to try a lot of different types of food. I went with 2 other people and we all tried something different and then shared.  I'm adding to my review because of the extremely fun and relaxing afternoon we had here on Bastille Day. I found the event on Eventbrite and we went there to check it out. We ended up buying a picnic which consisted of a canvas tote with a baguette, fromage, and a bottle of rosé. We sat under an umbrella all afternoon eating and drinking while watching this fantastic mime interact with people. The mime was an exceptional performer. They did a fantastic job making it a welcoming, relaxing, space. They laid out carpets and several pillows and blankets for people to sit on under two big umbrellas. I was so stressed earlier and it all melted away. I am keeping an eye out for other events here because it's been several days now and I'm still feeling good about our afternoon there. I can't wait to see what other events they have.

Bow Market is one of those places that you didn’t know your area needed, but now that it’s here you can’t imagine not having it?  The first floor is a ton of small food shops (read: no seating in the individual food places) and they’re all delicious. You can get anything from poutine to pierogis to Korean bbq to empanadas and more. There’s also an excellent brewery and a badass wine bar.  The second floor is all unique, local artist shops and vintage stores. The stock appears to change monthly and everything the artists sell is gorgeous! There’s also a comedy club / cocktail bar up there too.  This is one of those places that you’re like “What?” until you visit and then never want to leave. Especially when the weather’s nice and you can spend the whole day eating and drinking outside. With your dog. Because they’re very dog friendly as long as you don’t bring your furry friend into the little food places :)
